I am so excited to announce that @dr_lipman , owner of the Atlanta Fibroid Center, and I have partnered to bring more awareness around Uterine Fibroid Embolization. I will now be the brand ambassador for the Atlanta Fibroid Center, where our goal is to educate and support women on the importance of knowing about Uterine Fibroid Embolization and what to do next! 

Dr. John Lipman is taking charge and has made it his mission to educate women about uterine fibroids and the non-surgical treatments that he offers. It is my goal to be transparent and authentic, in hopes of answering questions for women who suffer with this very common diagnosis. Through my transparency, I hope I can be a helping hand to women all around the world!

For more information on all that Dr. Lipman does, be sure to add them on instagram @dr_lipman!

The partnership between @dr_lipman and I was crafted to spread awareness to women about fibroids and alternate solutions that you may or may not have heard about, yet. Dr. Lipman is the founder of the Atlanta Fibroid Center, where he specializes in a non-surgical procedure; Uterine Fibroid Embolization (UFE), that is performed instead of hysterectomies, to allow women the opportunity to keep their uterus! He's on a passionate mission to spread awareness around this,  and it's life-changing, and through our collaboration, it's also my mission to spread awareness and support women. Join us as we embark this new journey together, we're excited to spread awareness, offer support and insight, as well as, inform women that they have a CHOICE!

Partnering with @dr_lipman has been the most inspiring collaboration to date. Dr. Lipman is extremely passionate about his mission to spread awareness about uterine fibroids and the life-changing procedure that he offers- Uterine Fibroid Embolization. Uterine Fibroid Embolization, also known as, UFE is a minimally-invasive alternative to hysterectomy and myomectomy.

  I’ve decided to share my story because I want to raise awareness about uterine fibroids and encourage women to advocate for themselves when it comes to their health. It's okay to ask questions and seek out second opinions, and it's important to know that you have options.

Join our weekly IG Live series, “Dear Destiny” every Friday at 1:30 pm, where Dr. Lipman and I talk about health-related questions about fibroids and other health-related questions! #fibroidsawareness #drlipman #atlantafibroidcenter #destinypayton #itsLAW

@thedestinypayton is a woman after my own heart. We can’t stop creating. Creating is like breathing 😮‍💨! I’m so happy to welcome @thedestinypayton to @womenoftmro  with @_kaydane_ 

Destiny is a mother, an actor, personality, host and musician, who truly doesn’t let anyone or anything stop her. 

Such a chill and real conversation about all things women, not to mention a woman living her life in front of the world. 

#womenoftmro #allthingswomenloading #poweredbytmro #renaissance

Pay your bills or feed your soul?? This is the question! 

Some advice that was given to @thedestinypayton was to “get good at one thing before starting another”, but that’s not always easy when searching for the sweet spot between financial stability and soul fulfillment. 

Your vision is not meant for everyone to see and that’s just fine, because it’s YOUR vision.

Navigating life is not a cookie cutter experience. You gotta do what works for you and trust yourself to see it through.

#womenoftmro #poweredbytmro #podcast #worklifebalance

Let’s talk about wearing All the Hats! That’s how most of us have to start, but the goal is to build a dynamic team that can embrace your vision, add to it when necessary and help execute it. 

HOW MANY HATS DO YOU WEAR? 

We look at our cultural icons as a 1 woman/man show when in truth, there is an army of people helping them show up in the way they do for the world. 

@thedestinypayton spoke in the most transparent ways and included that she does need help, but she won’t let it stop her.  Her podcast named “Unbreakable” is a testament to keep going even after situations are meant to break you. 

The ultimate goal is a village, a team, a support system to help us all be our best and let others do what they do best. 

Happy Wednesday and subscribe to our YT for this episode with Destiny dropping this Sunday.

On this #FallBackFriday I share the start of my journey into the beauty industry. Before I hit y'all's Tv screens...this is my first photoshoot (over a decade ago) for a product my then partner and I had with a provisional patent. Shopping this product introduced me to the beauty supply world, thus birthing @madonnibeauty I am proud to say I became the first black woman to have a beauty supply & salon suites in Alabama, no matter the trials, tribulations, pivots and perceived failures or as I say...lessons learned. The fact remains that I DID THAT! And I ain't done yet...only stronger and wiser. I pray that my journey can inspire and teach as I continue to grow and evolve. This vision was given to me by GOD and HIS promises are real...no man can stop that!
